      "content": "Unpredictable, jittery resets without clear inactivity usually suggest underlying network instability or resource constraints. Consider checking for network interface errors or packet loss metrics exposed by AWS CloudWatch for the specific ENI attached to your instance. Additionally, misconfigurations in routing tables or overlapping IP ranges in a complex VPC setup can sometimes introduce intermittent packet drops that mimic connection resets.",
